  "body": "<!--\r\nNeed help?\r\nRefer to our contributing guidelines for additional information about making a good issue:\r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum-optimism/.github/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md\r\n-->\r\n\r\n**Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.**\r\nSome files in the integration tests still use an older method of importing contract artifacts directly instead of going through `hardhat-ethers`. For example, [basic-l1-l2-communication.spec.ts](https://github.com/ethereum-optimism/optimism/blob/develop/integration-tests/test/basic-l1-l2-communication.spec.ts) includes the following import:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum-optimism/optimism/blob/e634bf2ca62b895db678531c4488aa2d2e2e1a2c/integration-tests/test/basic-l1-l2-communication.spec.ts#L8\r\n\r\nThis file then creates a contract factory using the JSON object imported from this file:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum-optimism/optimism/blob/e634bf2ca62b895db678531c4488aa2d2e2e1a2c/integration-tests/test/basic-l1-l2-communication.spec.ts#L25-L29\r\n\r\nThis is not clean.\r\n\r\n**Describe the solution you'd like**\r\nIt's cleaner to replace this with the functionality already provided by the `hardhat-ethers` plugin. Simply import `ethers` from `hardhat`:\r\n\r\n```ts\r\nimport { ethers } from 'hardhat'\r\n```\r\n\r\nThen import the factory from `ethers`:\r\n\r\n```ts\r\nconst SimpleStorageFactory = await ethers.getContractFactory('SimpleStorage')\r\n```\r\n\r\nDoing this allows us to remove the long (and brittle) JSON imports. Please check other `.spec.ts` files within `integration-tests/test` to see if there are other places where this can also be fixed. :heart: \r\n",
